## Conversation
User asked: "Add an import linter to ban the trace server from importing client
code and vice versa. Workers should also not be allowed to import from the rest
of the client. Do not move code, just add the linter and flag the violations.
Then add ignores to the linter temporarily. We will remove these later as we
work on untangling the repo." Then: "put this up as draft."

Intent: stand up enforcement of the trace_server <-> client SDK boundary and a
workers -> client boundary, WITHOUT refactoring import relationships. Freeze the
current entanglement as temporary ignores that form an untangling backlog.

## Actions
- Mapped boundaries. client = every top-level weave package except trace_server
  and shared. shared is the intentional NEUTRAL zone (it imports weave.trace but
  never weave.trace_server) -> excluded from "client" so its imports are not
  noise. Confirmed later: 0 shared entries in the violation set.
- `uv venv --python 3.12` (3.14 default can't build tiktoken), `uv add --group
  dev "import-linter>=2.0"` -> import-linter 2.6 / grimp 3.13.
- Added [tool.importlinter] to pyproject.toml: 3 forbidden contracts
  (trace_server->client, client->trace_server, workers->client), each with
  allow_indirect_imports=true (direct edges only) and explicit client package
  lists. unmatched_ignore_imports_alerting left at default (error).
- Ran lint-imports with empty ignores, parsed the report into per-contract
  ignore lists, pasted them back. 15 + 65 + 5 = 85 edges.
- Added prek hook 'import-linter' (entry: uv run lint-imports) mirroring the ty
  hook. gitignored .import_linter_cache / .grimp_cache.
- Verified: lint-imports 3 kept/0 broken; ty (whole repo) pass; ruff (whole
  repo) pass; import weave + submodules import fine; YAML/TOML parse.
- Committed (chore(weave): ...), gt track --parent master, gt submit --draft
  --no-interactive --no-edit --no-stack --no-verify -> PR #7334 (draft).

## Errors & Mistakes
- BIGGEST surprise: grimp (import-linter's graph engine) silently PRUNES PEP 420
  implicit namespace packages (dirs without __init__.py) AND all their subdirs
  (grimp/adaptors/modulefinder.py lines 43-46). First graph had 310 modules with
  trace_server_bindings, flow, chat, compat AND deep dirs (trace/context,
  trace_server/query_builder, trace_server/agents, interface/builtin_object_classes,
  workers, ...) entirely INVISIBLE. A contract naming a missing module errors
  ('Module X does not exist'); imports TO a pruned module are dropped (silently
  unflagged). Fix: added 22 empty __init__.py to restore a contiguous package
  chain -> graph 310 -> 441 modules. grimp itself recommends this. Behavior-
  preserving (empty files, full-path imports unchanged, import weave + ty green).
  NOT 'moving code'. This is the single most important thing to know here.
- Parser regex bug: required a single '(l.NN)'; missed edges with multiple line
  numbers '(l.46, l.47)'. Dropped 2 contract-2 edges (evaluation.eval ->
  trace_server_interface; flow.saved_view -> interface.builtin_object_classes.saved_view).
  Caught because lint-imports then reported exactly those 2 as broken. Re-parsed
  with '... -> (weave\\.\\S+?)\\s*\\(l\\.' to get 65.
- Stale graph cache: the FIRST lint-imports run (before __init__.py existed)
  cached a 310-module graph in .import_linter_cache. My manual reruns used
  --no-cache so they passed, but the prek hook (no --no-cache) read the stale
  cache and errored 'No matches for ignored import ... -> weave.trace.context...'
  (unmatched_ignore_imports_alerting=error). grimp's cache did NOT invalidate on
  newly-ADDED __init__.py. Fix: rm -rf the cache; it rebuilds correctly. A fresh
  clone never hits this (no pre-existing stale cache). gitignored the cache dirs.
- zsh does not word-split unquoted $var -> a 'for d in $DIRS; touch ...' loop
  fed touch one giant newline string. Used printf | while read instead.

## Dead Ends
- Tried grimp.build_graph("weave","weave.flow",...) to include namespace pkgs as
